      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tap each round three times before moving on. Total: about five minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How it adapts",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rewrite the lines to name what's actually true today. \"I keep running numbers\" can become \"I keep checking the overdraft\" or \"I'm bracing for the rent direct debit.\" The eight-point structure holds; the words are adjustable.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you can't tap aloud, on the train, in the office bathroom, in bed next to a sleeping partner, say the lines silently. The tapping itself still works.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When the hands are full or cold, tap one-sided with the same hand cycling through the points. The script works the same way.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When five minutes isn't available, run the karate chop and one tapping round only. Skip the reframe. The shorter version takes ninety seconds and takes the edge off.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When this isn't working",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If a tapping round on its own isn't shifting the worry, pair it with an energy statement. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "I am allowed to want this",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/i-am-allowed-to-want-this"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " works well after this script. For a weekly reset rather than a daily one, use ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "the Calm & Safe Money Reset",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/the-calm-and-safe-money-reset"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From Day 1 of MONEY: A 12-Week Tapping Program (Rebecca J Page, 2025), p. 29. The eight-line tapping round and the eight-line reframe round are reproduced from the source; the surrounding framing is condensed for the library.",
            "type": "text"
          }
